---[ forest ]------------------------------------------------------------------

First of all, I apologize for the badness of this source code since it
is my very first python script.



usage: forest.py [options]

options:
  -h, --help       show this help message and exit
  --parser=PARSER  parser
  --style=STYLE    checking style
  --output=FILE    output file
  --output-pure    output a pure summary
  --output-detail  output a detailed summary



The '--parser' option is used to specify the parser to use. The parser
modules are located in the parsers/ directory. Once the parser is specified
with the '--parser' option, more options will be available.

The '--style' option specifies the coding style to use. The styles modules
are located in the styles/ directory. Once the style is specified, more
options will be available.

The '--output' option specifies where to place the ouptut. If this option
is not present, the standard output is used.

The '--output-pure' option is used to ouptut a very simple summary only
containing the error messages.

The '--output-detail' option is used to ouptut a more detailed summary
in xml format.
